text: as kid eatin reviews Idi Jang is less
daunting for beginners because of its
clear menus and automix button many
special effects are available purchased
with vinyl tokens earned by sharing
mixes signing the app up to Facebook or
cash as your skills improve you might
find yourself limited and the token
system could irritate you an alternative
is DJ Studio 5 this app looks simpler
than edy jiaying but it's full of
features like built-in special effects
automatic tempo syncing and Auto mixing
the design of the interface and controls
can be confusing to navigate and could
lead to multiple fails if you were using
the app to broadcast music to a party of
people for the true beginner there's the
party monster this app lets you build a
playlist of music for a party through a
simple touch interface it lists your
available music and then simply drag the
tracks into the to be played list once
they're lined up your songs will play
automatically fading between the end of
one and the start of another
